{{no footnotes|date=May 2016}}
[[File:Museo Historico Provincial Dr. Julio Marc.jpg|right|250px|thumb|Dr. Julio Marc Provincial Historical Museum]]
The '''Dr. Julio Marc Provincial Historical Museum''' (in Spanish, '''''Museo Histórico Provincial Dr. Julio Marc''''') is a [[museum]] in [[Rosario]], [[Argentina]]. It comprises more than 30 rooms hosting collections of archaeological items, Spanish-American art, [[numismatics]], pre-Columbian textile and silverwork crafts, and weapons, complemented by archives, a library, and collections of historical newspapers and maps.
The museum is located within the grounds of the [[Parque de la Independencia]]. It is administered by the government of the [[provinces of Argentina|province]] of [[Santa Fe Province|Santa Fe]]. It was founded in 1939, during the governorship of [[Manuel Iriondo]], and received the name of Julio Marc, its first director. The architect of the neo-classical structure was [[Ángel Guido]].
==References== * [https://web.archive.org/web/20060715003743/http://www.museosargentinos.org.ar/museos/museo.asp?codigo=220 Dr. Julio Marc Provincial History Museum of Rosario] at ''Museos Argentinos''. * {{es icon}} [http://www.santafe.gov.ar/cultura/organis/museos.htm#mar Museo Histórico Provincial "Dr. Julio Marc"] at the website of the Ministry of Culture of the Province of Santa Fe.
==External links== * [http://www.museomarc.gob.ar/ Official site] {{es icon}}
