{{Orphan|date=February 2013}} {{Lowercase title}} {{Infobox company |logo = mycityvenue.png | name = mycityvenue | owner = Secret Escapes | foundation = 2011 | founder = [[William Sachiti]] | location_city = [[London]] | location_country = United Kingdom | homepage = {{URL|http://www.mycityvenueescapes.com/}} | caption = | num_employees = 200+ | registration = }} '''mycityvenue''' is a UK-based experiences website offering things to do across the UK and other cities in Europe. mycityvenue initially launched as an events site and putting on parties across the UK such as [[Azealia Banks]] in [[The Old Vic Tunnels]], [[London Fashion Week]] after-parties and their own city festival. The company also created one off events featuring artists and performers including [[Morcheeba]], [[Noisettes]], [[Delilah (musician)]], [[Trevor Nelson]], [[Zalon]], [[Amy Winehouse]], and several more.<ref>[http://uk.prweb.com/releases/2013/9/prweb11130915.htm Apartment 58 – London's Newest Member's Club and Creative Hub announces Playtime Music Festival – A Boutique City Music Experience <!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref><ref>[http://www.mycityvenue.com/Apartment58/PlaytimeBoutiqueCityFestivalFriday-933 Friday At Playtime – The Boutique City Festival <!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> As well as their ticketed events, mycityvenue works a [[pay-per-click]] model with its partners. The website switched to a pay per reservation structure in 2013 with over 1200 UK venues see.<ref>[http://www.thetechbulletin.com/secret-escapes-secures-60m-from-google-ventures-27551 Secret Escapes secures $60M from Google Ventures <!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> mycityvenue publishes a weekly [[newsletter]] which is circulated to is 1.4 million subscribers.
== History == mycityvenue was founded by entrepreneur [[William Sachiti]] and launched in 2011 as UK-based event search which lets users find and book a night out, pitching itself as a kind of ‘digital concierge service’ by consolidating the whole process and moving it online.<ref>[http://performancein.com/news/2015/07/28/secret-escapes-claims-38-million-investors-including-google/ Secret Escapes Claims £38 Million from Investors Including Google <!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> After travel company [[Secret Escapes]] raised $13 million from Google, Index Ventures, Octopus Ventures and Atlas mycityvenue was acquired in an all-cash-and-stock deal.<ref>https://techcrunch.com/2014/07/24/secret-acquisition A Secret Acquisition</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://fortune.com/2014/07/25/term-sheet-friday-july-25/|title=Term Sheet – Friday, July 25|last=Primack|first=Dan|date=25 July 2014|work=Fortune}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://startups.co.uk/young-guns/secret-escapes-acquires-city-venue-strengthen-events-arm/|title=Secret Escapes acquires My City Venue to strengthen events arm|last=Dunsby|first=Megan|date=25 July 2014|publisher=Startups}}</ref>
