{{italic title}}
'''The Filmgoer's Companion''', now published as '''''Halliwell's Who's Who in the Movies''''', is an encyclopedic reference of film [[actors]], film technicians (cameramen, editors, score composers, and the many other specialist required to make a movie), [[film directors|directors]] and [[film producer|producers]] who have produced or performed in the cinema.  The format is a brief biographic introduction, followed by a list of films that they have association. It was originally written by [[Leslie Halliwell]], but since his death in 1989, it has been edited by John Walker.

The second half of the book contains information on film themes and genres, a listing of production companies and [[film studios]], a glossary, and some [[movie award]]s.

The first edition was published in 1965 and included an introduction by [[Alfred Hitchcock]].

==Latest edition==
The 4th edition of ''Halliwell's Who's Who in the Movies'' (i.e. the 16th edition of ''The Filmgoer's Companion'') (2006) ({{ISBN|0007169574}}) contains 656 pages.

